# Trivy misconfiguration waivers, documented and evidence-based.
# Installed by sscsb's `fuzzing` control (kept if you already have a .trivyignore).
#
# Each entry is a case where Trivy's generic *runtime*-container rules
# fundamentally CANNOT model the artifact — NOT a "safe in practice" waiver.
# Every finding on code you actually control should be fixed at the code level
# (e.g. the ClusterFuzzLite base image is pinned by digest, not waived here).
#
# .clusterfuzzlite/Dockerfile is the OSS-Fuzz / ClusterFuzzLite *build* container
# — the only artifact class that makes OpenSSF Scorecard's FuzzingID detectable
# for Rust. Full rationale lives next to the code in that Dockerfile's header.
#
# DS-0002 — "Image user should not be 'root'": gcr.io/oss-fuzz-base/base-builder-rust
#   REQUIRES root. The OSS-Fuzz toolchain and ClusterFuzzLite's runner compile
#   into root-owned $OUT/$SRC/$WORK; a non-root USER breaks the fuzz build, and
#   there is no root-free way to produce Scorecard-detectable Rust fuzzing.
DS-0002
# DS-0026 — "No HEALTHCHECK defined": this build container exits after compiling
#   the fuzz targets; it runs no long-lived service, so a HEALTHCHECK is a
#   category error, not a missing control.
DS-0026
